<H4>Singly Even Magic Squares</H4>
<P>Well it seems we have encountered another phrase that isn't very =
descriptive.=20
 Basically, "singly even" means divisible by 2 but not by four.  A =
formula for=20
generating singly even numbers is (n*4) + 2, which generates the numbers =
2, 6,=20
10, 14, 18, 22, 26, 30 and so on.  There is no magic square that can be=20
constructed in a 2 by 2 square but singly even magic squares can be =
constructed=20
for n=3D6, 10, 14 and so on.   =20
